# Builder reference

Use the curated digests in `docs/builder-reference/` when changing convmem
architecture, retrieval, or debugging workflow.

## Read this when

- touching module boundaries, CLI surfaces, or MCP handlers
- changing ranking, chunking, or evaluation behavior
- changing triage, reproduction, or verification flow
- evaluating service splits, data ownership, or ingest/watch boundaries
- F1 refine job queue, tombstones, ledger/Chroma replication
- adding or modifying automated checks, fitness functions, or threshold gates

## Tier A (on-demand — Cursor pointer / Crush builder-reference/)

- `docs/builder-reference/ousterhout-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/manning-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/zeller-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/hard-parts-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/ddia-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/arch-patterns-python-builder-digest.md`
- `docs/builder-reference/evolutionary-architectures-builder-digest.md`

## Tier B

Read the relevant digest first, then make the change. Keep the protocol rules
lean; put book knowledge in the digests.
